definition.value: A 3-D-galactosyl glycerol in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydrogen has beta configuration.
A disaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose and D-galactopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A molecular entity that can transfer an electron to another molecular entity.
An amino disaccharide consisting of alpha-L-threo-hex-4-enopyranuronic acid and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
